      "turn": 1,
      "actor": "user",
      "content": "You are a subagent: gsd-executor. FIX: handleSessionIdle() for main sessions không update lastMessage.\n\n## Problem:\nIn `event-capture.ts`, `handleSessionIdle()` for main sessions (line 306-308) calls:\n```typescript\nawait this.sessionWriter.updateFrontmatter(sessionID, {\n  status: \"completed\",\n} as Partial<import(\"../types.js\").SessionRecord>)\n```\n\nThis ONLY updates `status` — it does NOT update `lastMessage`!\n\nThe `lastMessage` captured by `message-capture.ts` is stored in the `pendingRegistry` but is NEVER written to the MD file for main sessions.\n\n## Fix Required:\n\nIn `handleSessionIdle()`, before updating status, we need to:\n1. Get the lastMessage from `this.pendingRegistry.get(sessionID)`\n2. Pass it to `updateFrontmatter()` along with status\n\n## Implementation:\n\nAdd `lastMessage` to the update call:\n```typescript\nconst lastMessageEntry = this.pendingRegistry?.get(sessionID)\nconst lastMessage = Array.isArray(lastMessageEntry) \n  ? lastMessageEntry[0]?.lastMessage \n  : lastMessageEntry?.lastMessage\n\nawait this.sessionWriter.updateFrontmatter(sessionID, {\n  status: \"completed\",\n  lastMessage: lastMessage,\n} as Partial<import(\"../types.js\").SessionRecord>)\n```\n\nAfter fix:\n1. Run `npm run typecheck` — must pass\n2. Run `npm run build` — must pass  \n3. Run `npm test` — must pass\n\nReturn: confirmation of the fix and test results.",
